cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image completion using deep networks and adversarial training, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses unsupervised representation learning, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of adversarial loss and the novel "hide-and-seek" approach also suggests the possibility of graph theory (cs.GR) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper validates its models on several datasets, indicating the possibility of multimedia (cs.MM) being another relevant sub-category.
